The paper discusses the automatic generation of source code comments, which falls under the software engineering (cs.SE) sub-category. The algorithms and techniques used for automatic generation of comments involve natural language processing (NLP) and machine learning (ML), which are also relevant to programming languages (cs.PL), artificial intelligence (cs.AI), and machine learning (cs.LG) sub-categories. Additionally, the paper discusses the quality assessment of generated comments, which involves evaluating the language and coherence of the comments, making it relevant to the computational linguistics (cs.CL) sub-category.
